# GraphJudge Streamlit Pipeline - Environment Configuration Example
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual API credentials
# 
# IMPORTANT: Never commit your actual .env file with real API keys to version control!

# =============================================================================
# API CONFIGURATION - Choose ONE of the following options:
# =============================================================================

# Option 1: Azure OpenAI (Recommended for enterprise usage)
# If you have Azure OpenAI access, configure both of these:
# AZURE_OPENAI_KEY=your_azure_openai_api_key_here
# AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource-name.openai.azure.com/

# Option 2: Standard OpenAI API (Most common)
# If using standard OpenAI API, configure this:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Optional: Custom OpenAI API Base URL (only if using a proxy or custom endpoint)
# OPENAI_API_BASE=https://api.openai.com/v1

# =============================================================================
# PERPLEXITY API CONFIGURATION (Required for Graph Judgment)
# =============================================================================

# Perplexity API key for graph judgment functionality
# Get your key from: https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api
# PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=your_perplexity_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# ADDITIONAL API CONFIGURATIONS (Optional)
# =============================================================================

# If you need to use alternative judgment APIs, you can configure them here:

# KIMI API (Alternative judgment provider)
# KIMI_API_KEY=your_kimi_api_key_here

# Gemini API (Alternative judgment provider)
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS:
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Edit the .env file and uncomment the lines you need
# 3. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys
# 4. Save the file
#
# The application will automatically detect and load your configuration.
#
# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES:
# =============================================================================
#
# - Never share your API keys publicly
# - Add .env to your .gitignore file (already done in this project)
# - Use environment-specific keys (dev/staging/production)
# - Rotate your API keys regularly
# - Consider using Azure Key Vault or similar for production deployments
#
# =============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING:
# =============================================================================
#
# If you get "No valid API configuration found" errors:
# 1. Make sure your .env file is in the streamlit_pipeline/ directory
# 2. Check that you've uncommented the required lines (remove the # symbol)
# 3. Verify your API keys are valid and have sufficient credits/quota
# 4. For Azure OpenAI, ensure both KEY and ENDPOINT are configured
#
# For more help, see the project documentation or README.md